verify /ˈvɛrɪˌfaɪ/

(verifying,verified,verifies) 

1. V-T If you verify something, you check that it is true by careful examination or investigation. 核实 

例： I verified the source from which I had that information. 我核实了我获知那条信息的来源。 

2. verification N-UNCOUNT 核实 

例： All charges against her are dropped pending the verification of her story. 在她的陈述得到证实前，所有针对她的指控都被撤回。 

3. V-T If you verify something, you state or confirm that it is true. 证实 [no cont] 

例： The government has not verified any of those reports. 该政府尚未证实那些报道中的任何一个。

